# WoW AddOn Development Rules

This project is a World of Warcraft addon written in Lua.

## Common WoW API Functions
- `CreateFrame()` - Creates UI frames
- `C_Item.GetItemInfo()` - Gets item information
- `C_TradeSkillUI` - Trade skill/Profession API
- `Auctionator.API.v1` - Auctionator addon API for prices
- `GameTooltip` - Tooltip management
- `C_Timer.After()` - Delayed function execution

## Coding Style
- Use descriptive variable names
- Add comments for complex logic
- Follow WoW addon naming conventions

## Common Patterns
- Frames use `CreateFrame()` with optional templates
- Event handlers use `:SetScript("OnEvent", function(self, event, ...) end)`
- Localization uses `L(TEXT.KEY)` pattern
- Settings stored in saved variables via `addon:GetSetting()` / `addon:SetSetting()`
